This paper deals with wireless networks and their optimization, which is a topic that falls under the category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the joint design of transmission and caching policies, which involves information theory and communication systems, making Information Theory (cs.IT) another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with optimization problems, which is a topic that falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses caching of popular contents, which is a topic that falls under the category of Multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the caching of contents at small base stations and user terminals, which is a topic that falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
